# Dashboard RTL/LTR contract

Locale source: `DashLocaleProvider` in `App.tsx` — use `useDashLocale()` in admin components; do not pass `isFa` as props.

| Locale | Document `dir` | UI alignment | Sheet side | URLs / codes / mono | Date pickers |
|--------|----------------|--------------|------------|---------------------|--------------|
| **FA** | `rtl` | `text-start` (not `text-right`) | `left` | `dashLtrCell()` or `dir="ltr"` on cell | Jalali + `dir=rtl` via `DashboardDatePicker` / `DashboardDateTimePicker` |
| **EN** | `ltr` | `text-start` | `right` | same | Gregorian + `dir=ltr` (same facades) |

## Date pickers

- **Always** use `DashboardDatePicker` or `DashboardDateTimePicker` from `@/components/dashboard-datetime-picker` — never import `JalaliDateTimePicker` / `GregorianDateTimePicker` in admin pages.
- Calendar kind: `dashDatePickerCalendar(isFa)` → `jalali` | `gregorian`.
- Root + popover use `useDashLocale().dir`; stored API values stay **Gregorian ISO** (`datetime-api`).

## New pages

- Root: `<DashPage>` from `@/components/dash-page`
- Sheets: `<DashSheetContent>` from `@/components/dash-sheet-content`
- Dialogs: `<DashDialogContent>` / `DashDialogHeader` / `DashDialogFooter`
- Avoid: `text-right`, `text-left`, `flex-row-reverse` for RTL-only layout

## Example

```tsx
import { useDashLocale } from "@/lib/dash-locale-context"
import { DashPage } from "@/components/dash-page"
import { DashSheetContent } from "@/components/dash-sheet-content"

export function MyNewAdmin() {
  const { isFa, ltrCell } = useDashLocale()
  return (
    <DashPage>
      <DashSheetContent>...</DashSheetContent>
    </DashPage>
  )
}
```

